&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 4 i.e No improvement.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of &lt;strong&gt;V1&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &amp;#39;meet&amp;#39; after the preposition &amp;#39;to&amp;#39; is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The preposition &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to&amp;#39; is followed by the base form of the verb.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the given sentence is grammatically correct and it needs no improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;prospect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outlook&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a person&amp;#39;s perspective, attitude, or expectations about the future. It can also refer to the general state of affairs or the way in which something is likely to develop or unfold.&amp;nbsp; (आउटलुक भविष्य के बारे में किसी व्यक्ति के दृष्टिकोण, या अपेक्षाओं को संदर्भित करता है। यह सामान्य स्थिति को भी संदर्भित कर सकता है या जिस तरह से कुछ विकसित या प्रकट होने की संभावना है।)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: A person&amp;#39;s outlook on life, which can be optimistic, pessimistic, or neutral.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If someone is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;looking out&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; for someone else, it means that they are watching over them, protecting them, or taking care of them. (अगर कोई किसी और के लिए &amp;quot;देख रहा है&amp;quot;, इसका मतलब है कि वे उन पर नजर रख रहे हैं, उनकी रक्षा कर रहे हैं, या उनकी देखभाल कर रहे हैं।)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: Parents might say &amp;quot;I&amp;#39;m always&lt;strong&gt; looking out &lt;/strong&gt;for my children&amp;#39;s best interests.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prospect&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the possibility or likelihood of something happening or occurring in the future, often in a context of potential or opportunity. (संभावना भविष्य में होने या घटित होने की संभावना&amp;nbsp; को संदर्भित करती है, अक्सर संभावित या अवसर के संदर्भ में।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;prospect&lt;/strong&gt; of a new job or career opportunity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outward appearance&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the way that something or someone looks on the outside, especially in relation to how others perceive it or them. It is often used to describe the surface-level or first impression that someone or something makes. (बाहरी दिखावट से तात्पर्य उस तरीके से है जिससे कोई चीज या कोई व्यक्ति बाहर की ओर देखता है, विशेष रूप से इस संबंध में कि दूसरे इसे या उन्हें कैसे देखते हैं। इसका उपयोग अक्सर सतह-स्तर या पहली छाप का वर्णन करने के लिए किया जाता है जो कोई या कुछ बनाता है।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: The &lt;strong&gt;outward appearance&lt;/strong&gt; of a person, including factors such as clothing, grooming, and physical appearance.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scrutiny&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the act of carefully examining or inspecting something, often in a critical or skeptical manner.&amp;nbsp; (स्क्रूटनी का तात्पर्य किसी चीज की सावधानीपूर्वक जांच या निरीक्षण करने के कार्य से है, जो अक्सर आलोचनात्मक या संदेहपूर्ण तरीके से होता है।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: The financial &lt;strong&gt;scrutiny&lt;/strong&gt; of a company by investors to determine whether to buy its stock.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;According to the meanings of the given words,&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2, i.e.,&amp;nbsp; prospect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer &lt;strong&gt;beginning and end.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;The Alpha and Omega&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is taken from Christianity and&amp;nbsp;refers&amp;nbsp;to Jesus.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Alpha&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is the first letter of Greek alphabet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Omega&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the last letter of Greek alphabet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the meaning of the idiom is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;The beginning and the end&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Passive voice structure: The object of the active voice sentence becomes the subject of the passive voice sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the active voice, the sentence is: &amp;quot;Every citizen must follow the traffic rules strictly to ensure safety on the roads.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;To convert to passive voice: Place the object &amp;quot;the traffic rules&amp;quot; at the beginning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Change the active verb form &amp;quot;must follow&amp;quot; to &amp;quot;must be followed&amp;quot; (modal passive construction).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Add the preposition &amp;quot;by&amp;quot; followed by the original subject &amp;quot;every citizen.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Ensure the additional phrase &amp;quot;to ensure safety on the roads&amp;quot; remains intact at the end for clarity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;The traffic rules must be followed strictly by every citizen to ensure safety on the roads.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;The traffic rules are followed strictly by every citizen to ensure safety on the roads.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Incorrect tense (present simple passive).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;The traffic rules were followed strictly by every citizen to ensure safety on the roads.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Incorrect tense (past simple passive).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;The traffic rules have been followed strictly by every citizen to ensure safety on the roads.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Incorrect tense (present perfect passive).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Stationery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Stationery&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means materials (such as paper, pens, and ink) for writing or typing.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example:-&amp;nbsp;Amid the glare of the cameras, Britain&amp;rsquo;s King Charles III seems to be having trouble with his &lt;strong&gt;stationery&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/confusion-points-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Confusion Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stationary&lt;/strong&gt; means &amp;#39;not moving&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other words are wrongly spelt&amp;nbsp;and are not denoting&amp;nbsp;the given meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Standards&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s have a look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the given word:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ethos &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;the characteristic spirit of a culture, era, or community as manifested in its attitudes and aspirations.(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;प्रकृति)&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For Example - It is a challenge to the ethos of the 1960s.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s have a look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the other words given in the options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standards &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;principles of conduct informed by notions of honour and decency.(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;मानक)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Break &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;separate or cause to separate into pieces as a result of a blow, shock, or strain.(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;तोड़ना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulations &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;a rule or directive made and maintained by an authority.(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;विनियमन)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prestige &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;widespread respect and admiration felt for someone or something on the basis of a perception of their achievements or quality.(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;प्रतिष्ठा)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Substantial&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Paltry&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means too small to be considered important or useful.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;They worked long hours for &lt;strong&gt;paltry &lt;/strong&gt;wages.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Marked option&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Substantial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means large in amount or a strong thing.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;The storms caused &lt;strong&gt;substantial &lt;/strong&gt;damage.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is clear that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Paltry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Substantial&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are opposite in meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2.​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Key&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;something that helps you achieve or understand something.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Crucial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means an&amp;nbsp;extremely important thing.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Basic&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;the simplest kind or level; including only what is necessary without anything extra.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct solution is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The wine has not been tasted by me&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The sentence&lt;em&gt; &amp;#39;I have not tasted the wine&amp;#39; &lt;/em&gt;is an &lt;strong&gt;active voice&lt;/strong&gt; in a &lt;strong&gt;present perfect tense, (Subject+ has\have+ third form of verb+ object)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We have to convert this into a passive voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When converting it into&lt;strong&gt; passive voice&lt;/strong&gt;, the rules are:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The object of the sentence will come first followed by has been/have been.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Next comes the third form of the verb.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The sentence end with the subject. However instead of the Pronoun&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;I&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;used in the active voice, the pronoun&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &amp;#39;me&amp;#39; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;will be used instead.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The passive voice will the be in the form-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Object+ has been/ have been+ third form of verb+ by+ subject.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence will thus become&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;The wine(object) + has not been+ tasted (third form of verb)+ by+ me(subject).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence the correct answer is &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 3.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Evasive&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means trying to avoid something; not direct.(टालने वाला)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-His&amp;nbsp;answers were evasive and didn&amp;#39;t address the real issue.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Ambiguous&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;having more than one possible meaning, unclear&amp;nbsp;or confusing.(अस्पष्ट)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-He gives an ambiguous answer to his initial question.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that synonym of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;evasive&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;ambiguous&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;Ambiguous&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meaning and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cohesive&lt;/strong&gt;(जोड़नेवाला):&amp;nbsp;united and working together effectively

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-A &lt;strong&gt;cohesive &lt;/strong&gt;team works well together and supports each other.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accessible&lt;/strong&gt;(पहुंच योग्य):&amp;nbsp;possible to be reached or entered
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-The site is &lt;strong&gt;accessible &lt;/strong&gt;by a choice of means of transport.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abrasive&lt;/strong&gt;(अपघर्षक):&amp;nbsp;rough and likely to scratch
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-The&amp;nbsp;wood should be rubbed down with fine &lt;strong&gt;abrasive &lt;/strong&gt;paper.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

