&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;option 2 i.e. B.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;There is no error in Part &amp;#39;A&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;C&amp;#39; of the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;It simply tells about the facial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  text-align: justify; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;recognition tracking (FRT) system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;There is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an error&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part &amp;#39;B&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence. The sentence is written in &lt;strong&gt;present perfect continuous, that is wrong.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Present perfect continuous tense&lt;/strong&gt; is used to say &lt;strong&gt;how long for unfinished actions which started in the past and continue to the present.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The given sentence doesn&amp;#39;t represent unfinished action,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;so &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;increasing&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; should be replaced by &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;increased&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
