	&lt;li&gt;Part&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;B&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;which adds who the brainchild behind IPL was should come after sentence&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;A&lt;/strong&gt;, to maintain continuity on the topic and because it begins with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;conjunction and.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Part&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the concluding part of the sentence as it provides further information regarding Lalit Modi.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct order after rearrangement is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 4 i.e. CABD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So, the correct sentence is :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(C)&amp;nbsp;The Indian Premier League (IPL) was founded by (A) the Board of Control for Cricket&amp;nbsp;in India (BCCI) in 2008 (B) and is regarded as the brainchild of Lalit Modi, the founder (D) and former commissioner of the league.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(88, 89, 91);   font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;In the following question, there are six parts marked S1, S6, P, Q, R, and S. The position of S1 and S6 are fixed. some parts of the sentence have been jumbled up. Rearrange these parts and choose the proper sequence from the given options.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(S1)&amp;nbsp;Jane Austen was born on 16 December 1775.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;(P) Steventon is situated in the undulating, lightly forested country between two roads from Basingstoke&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;(Q) She was the daughter of a country minister in Steventon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;(R) in Steventon a small Hampshire town in south-central England.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;(S) one running almost west to Andover, the other southwest to Winchester.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;(S6) She died in 1817.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;RPSQ&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;R follows S1, it connects&amp;nbsp;S1 it tells about the place where Jane was born.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;P follows R, it further described the city of Steventon. Which&amp;nbsp;is situated in a forested country between two roads from Basingstoke.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;S follows P, it connects P by further describing those two roads from Basingstoke where Steventon is situated.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Q follows S. It tells about Jane Austen that she is the daughter of the Minister. It is independent information of all other sentences so it will be next to S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus the correct sequence is,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;S1.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Jane Austen was born on 16 December 1775.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;R.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in Steventon a small Hampshire town in south-central England.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;P.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Steventon is situated in the undulating, lightly forested country between two roads from Basingstoke&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;S.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;one running almost west to Andover, the other southwest to Winchester.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Q.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;She was the daughter of a country minister in Steventon.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;S6.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;She was the daughter of a country minister in Steventon.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt;Correct Arrangement: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;S1RPSQS6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
